# ŸêŸêYoutube Downloader with aria

A simple script to download videos from YouTube using youtube-dl and aria2.

## Requirements

- Python 3
- youtube-dl
- aria2
- tqdm

## Usage

To download a video from a given URL, run the script with the -d or --download option followed by the URL. For example:

```bash
python youtubedl.py -d https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9bZkp7q19f0
```

The script will create a file with the following format:

[upload_date][id] title (by uploader).ext

For example:

[20120715][9bZkp7q19f0] PSY - GANGNAM STYLE(Í∞ïÎÇ®Ïä§ÌÉÄÏùº) M/V (by officialpsy).mp4

The script will also show a progress bar for each video download.

